OL,6,FNHS hospitals are discharging patients
OL,7,Finto hotels to ease the demand for
OL,8,Fhospital beds.
OL,10,FAt least three NHS trusts in the south
OL,11,Fwest of England are using "care hotels"
OL,12,Fto move patients who no longer need
OL,13,Furgent treatment but require social
OL,14,Fcare to free up beds for incoming
OL,15,Fpatients.
OL,17,FDischarged patients facing an average
OL,18,Fwait in the hotels of around a month
OL,19,Fbefore they can receive the care they
OL,20,Frequire in their own homes, or find
OL,21,Faccommodation in a care home.
